spans.text: I heard the tender sighs , " I seemed to join the plaintive cries " Of hapless youths , who through the myrtle grove " Bewail for ever their unfinished love : " To that unjoyous clime , " Torn from the sight of these etherial skies

The sons of earth , the vulgar crew , "
" Enough to rear such rustic lays " As foes
my claim ; And , more to cheer my drooping frame , She mixed the balm of opening flowers ; Such as the bee , with chemic powers , From Hybla's fragrant hill inhales , Or scent Sabea's blooming vales
On other plains , or near less verdant shades
the vernal store , Falls not a plume
